4. Visualizations

Distribution of Numeric Features

data %>%
  select(all_of(numeric_features)) %>%
  gather(key = "Feature", value = "Value") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Value)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 30, fill = "lightblue", color = "black") +
  facet_wrap(~ Feature, scales = "free") +
  theme_minimal() +
  ggtitle("Distribution of Numeric Features")

Placement Counts Bar Chart

ggplot(data, aes(x = Placement)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "lightgreen") +
  theme_minimal() +
  ggtitle("Count of Placed vs Not Placed Students")

Boxplots of Features by Placement

for (feature in numeric_features) {
  print(
    ggplot(data, aes_string(x = "Placement", y = feature, fill = "Placement")) +
      geom_boxplot() +
      theme_minimal() +
      ggtitle(paste("Boxplot of", feature, "by Placement"))
  )
}

corr_matrix <- cor(data[, numeric_features])

6. Statistical Significance Tests

T-tests for Numeric Features by Placement

for (feature in numeric_features) {
  t_test_result <- t.test(data[[feature]] ~ data$Placement)
  cat("\nT-test for feature:", feature, "\n")
  print(t_test_result)
}

Chi-square Test for Internship Experience and Placement

cat("\nContingency Table:\n")
## 
## Contingency Table:
print(table(data$Internship_Experience, data$Placement))
##      
##         No  Yes
##   No  5024 1012
##   Yes 3317  647
cat("\nChi-square Test Result:\n")
## 
## Chi-square Test Result:
chisq_test <- chisq.test(table(data$Internship_Experience, data$Placement))
print(chisq_test)
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test with Yates' continuity correction
## 
## data:  table(data$Internship_Experience, data$Placement)
## X-squared = 0.30979, df = 1, p-value = 0.5778
